  Lee Ainslie , chairman of the Robin
Hood Foundation, said the New York charity has received $8.5
million in donations since Nov. 2 following superstorm Sandy.  Ainslee, who runs hedge fund Maverick Capital Management
LP, spoke today in an interview on Bloomberg Television’s
“Market Makers” with Stephanie Ruhle and Erik Schatzker.  To contact the reporter on this story:
